# Agent Documentation

This directory contains agent-agnostic reference docs that both Claude Code and Codex (and any future LLM agent) load on demand.

## Why this structure exists

LLMs reliably follow ~150-200 instructions before degrading. If we put every rule in the root `CLAUDE.md`/`AGENTS.md`, we'd burn the budget on rules that don't apply to the current task.

Instead, we use **progressive disclosure**:

1. **Root files** (`CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`) - always loaded. Universal rules only. Kept slim.
2. **Skills + nested `AGENTS.md`** - auto-activated when relevant (skills via description matching, nested AGENTS.md via directory). Thin pointers to docs/ai/.
3. **`docs/ai/` reference docs** (this folder) - the source of truth. Loaded when the root files / skills tell the agent to.

See `writing-docs.md` for the full architecture and rules for editing these files.

